cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses caching popular contents at base stations to improve the performance of cellular networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper uses stochastic geometry theory to derive the area spectral efficiencies of the HetNets, which is a branch of information theory.
3. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper deals with improving the performance of cellular networks by comparing cache-enabled HetNets with conventional HetNets, which is a topic of interest in communication and networking.
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses the tradeoffs between cache-enabled HetNets and conventional HetNets, which can be viewed as a control problem in systems and control.
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper mentions the caching of popular contents, which is related to multimedia content delivery in cellular networks.
